## 4. Types.class Usage in AutoValueMoshiExtension.java (BASE code)

**Import at line 27:**
```java
import com.squareup.moshi.Types;
```

**Usage in `makeType()` method (lines 388-405):**
```java
private CodeBlock makeType(TypeName type) {
    CodeBlock.Builder block = CodeBlock.builder();
    if (type instanceof ParameterizedTypeName) {
      ParameterizedTypeName pType = (ParameterizedTypeName) type;
      block.add("$T.newParameterizedType($T.class", Types.class, pType.rawType);  // Line 392
      for (TypeName typeArg : pType.typeArguments) {
        if (typeArg instanceof ParameterizedTypeName) {
          block.add(", $L", makeType(typeArg));
        } else {
          block.add(", $T.class", typeArg);  // <-- PROBLEM: no WildcardTypeName handling!
        }
      }
      block.add(")");
    } else {
      block.add("$T.class", type);
    }
    return block.build();
  }
```

**Key finding:** The base `makeType()` method has **no handling for `WildcardTypeName`** — it only handles `ParameterizedTypeName` (recursive) and falls through to the generic `else` branch. This is exactly the bug the PR fixes.
